<font color="#FF0000">BRONZE P-38 AWARD</font><br>
<tt>Fri Aug 29  4:40:48 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br><br>
You guys are making fun of me, aren't you? Huh?  I know those things, I know you are, and here I was just about to award both of you the prestigious GRUNTS Bronze P-38 CCDC (consumed C-rats During Combat) Meritorious Unit Commendation. <br>
Unlike the Combat Action Ribbon given to all, even those with spit shine shoes, The coveted Bronze P-38 CCDC AWARD has been kept TOP SECRET for 30 years. <br>
Not even those who drank Agent Orange, burned shitters, dug trenches with their belt buckles, used C-4 as candles on pound cakes or those who sucked the air out of C-140 airplane tires knew of this award. <br>
Now, you two blew it. <br>
You would have gotten a T-shirt, Tickets to the worlds series, wouldn't have to vote or to pay taxes for two years. Now, you two blew it. <br>
It's all that warp speed and the blades on the chopper always going in the same direction that will cause that. Bet, no one ever told you, you had to unwind the chopper's blade in the opposite direction every 10,000 miles, did they. The Bronze P-38 would have entitled you to have someone do that for you. <br><br>
Blew it, big time, might have to fly backwards for a week to be reconsidered. <br>

<p><code>-- TOP SECRET  (Sparrowhawk) </code><p>


